    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>In certain instances, particularly in the case of θανατόω[b] and νεκρόω, it is difficult to determine whether the figurative meanings involved have become conventionalized or whether they represent what may be called figurative usage, in other words, new figures of speech which no doubt had become somewhat conventional for the Christian community.</Content>
